    12→# System Architecture Overview
    13→
    14→A fleet maintenance scheduling system requires careful architecture to handle optimization, data management, user interaction, and integration with external systems. This document provides the high-level architectural blueprint.
    15→
    16→## System Components
    17→
    18→### Core Architecture Diagram
    19→
    20→```
    21→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    22→│                           USER INTERFACE                                 │
    23→│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐│
    24→│  │   Dashboard  │  │   Schedule   │  │   What-If    │  │   Reports    ││
    25→│  │    Views     │  │    Editor    │  │  Simulator   │  │   Module     ││
    26→│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘│
    27→└────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
    28→                                 │ REST/GraphQL API
    29→┌────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┐
    30→│                           API LAYER                                      │
    31→│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐│
    32→│  │   Schedule   │  │    Asset     │  │  Analytics   │  │ Integration  ││
    33→│  │     API      │  │     API      │  │     API      │  │     API      ││
    34→│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘│
    35→└────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
    36→                                 │
    37→┌────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┐
    38→│                        SERVICE LAYER                                     │
    39→│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
    40→│  │                    Scheduling Service                             │  │
    41→│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐               │  │
    42→│  │  │   Master    │  │   Rolling   │  │   What-If   │               │  │
    43→│  │  │   Planner   │  │   Horizon   │  │   Engine    │               │  │
    44→│  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘               │  │
    45→│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
    46→│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐│
    47→│  │    Asset     │  │    Drift     │  │     RUC      │  │   Costing    ││
    48→│  │   Service    │  │   Tracker    │  │   Engine     │  │   Service    ││
    49→│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘│
    50→└────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
    51→                                 │
    52→┌────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┐
    53→│                      OPTIMIZATION LAYER                                  │
    54→│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
    55→│  │                    Solver Orchestrator                            │  │
    56→│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐               │  │
    57→│  │  │   HiGHS     │  │  CP-SAT     │  │  Heuristic  │               │  │
    58→│  │  │   Adapter   │  │  Adapter    │  │   Fallback  │               │  │
    59→│  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘               │  │
    60→│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
    61→└────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
    62→                                 │
    63→┌────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┐
    64→│                         DATA LAYER                                       │
    65→│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐│
    66→│  │  PostgreSQL  │  │ TimescaleDB  │  │    Redis     │  │    S3/Blob   ││
    67→│  │   (Assets)   │  │  (Metrics)   │  │   (Cache)    │  │   (Files)    ││
    68→│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘│
    69→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
    70→```
    71→
    72→### Component Responsibilities
    73→
    74→```typescript
    75→interface SystemComponents {
    76→  userInterface: {
    77→    dashboard: 'Real-time fleet status and KPIs';
    78→    scheduleEditor: 'View and modify maintenance schedule';
    79→    whatIfSimulator: 'Scenario planning interface';
    80→    reports: 'Scheduled and ad-hoc reporting';
    81→  };
    82→
    83→  apiLayer: {
    84→    scheduleApi: 'CRUD operations on schedules';
    85→    assetApi: 'Asset and maintenance type management';
    86→    analyticsApi: 'Metrics and KPI queries';
    87→    integrationApi: 'External system webhooks';
    88→  };
    89→
    90→  serviceLayer: {
    91→    schedulingService: 'Orchestrates schedule generation';
    92→    assetService: 'Asset lifecycle management';
    93→    driftTracker: 'Monitors planned vs actual';
    94→    rucEngine: 'Calculates usage recommendations';
    95→    costingService: 'Cost forecasting and tracking';
    96→  };
    97→
    98→  optimizationLayer: {
    99→    solverOrchestrator: 'Manages solver selection and execution';
   100→    highsAdapter: 'HiGHS MIP solver interface';
   101→    cpsatAdapter: 'OR-Tools CP-SAT interface';
   102→    heuristicFallback: 'Fast fallback algorithm';
   103→  };
   104→
   105→  dataLayer: {
   106→    postgresql: 'Relational data (assets, schedules)';
   107→    timescaledb: 'Time-series metrics';
   108→    redis: 'Session cache, job queues';
   109→    objectStorage: 'Reports, exports, backups';
   110→  };
   111→}
   112→```
   113→
   114→## Data Flow
   115→
   116→### Schedule Generation Flow
   117→
   118→```typescript
   119→interface ScheduleGenerationFlow {
   120→  step1_request: {
   121→    trigger: 'User action or scheduled job';
   122→    input: 'Schedule parameters, constraints';
   123→    output: 'Job ID for tracking';
   124→  };
   125→
   126→  step2_preparation: {
   127→    action: 'Load assets, maintenance types, current state';
   128→    source: 'PostgreSQL';
   129→    output: 'Problem instance';
   130→  };
   131→
   132→  step3_optimization: {
   133→    action: 'Solve scheduling problem';
   134→    solver: 'HiGHS or CP-SAT via orchestrator';
   135→    timeout: '60-300 seconds typical';
   136→    output: 'Optimized schedule';
   137→  };
   138→
   139→  step4_validation: {
   140→    action: 'Verify constraints satisfied';
   141→    checks: ['Capacity', 'Time windows', 'Precedence'];
   142→    output: 'Validated schedule or errors';
   143→  };
   144→
   145→  step5_persistence: {
   146→    action: 'Store schedule and metrics';
   147→    destination: 'PostgreSQL';
   148→    sideEffects: ['Invalidate caches', 'Trigger notifications'];
   149→  };
   150→
   151→  step6_response: {
   152→    action: 'Return result to caller';
   153→    content: 'Schedule summary and access URL';
   154→  };
   155→}
   156→```
   157→
   158→### Real-Time Monitoring Flow
   159→
   160→```typescript
   161→interface MonitoringFlow {
   162→  dataIngestion: {
   163→    sources: ['Telematics', 'Manual entry', 'EAM webhooks'];
   164→    frequency: 'Hourly to real-time';
   165→    destination: 'TimescaleDB';
   166→  };
   167→
   168→  driftCalculation: {
   169→    trigger: 'New mileage data received';
   170→    calculation: 'Actual - Planned mileage';
   171→    storage: 'Asset drift metrics';
   172→  };
   173→
   174→  rucGeneration: {
   175→    trigger: 'Daily or on drift threshold';
   176→    calculation: 'Categorize assets by drift';
   177→    output: 'ACCELERATE/NOMINAL/DECELERATE';
   178→  };
   179→
   180→  alerting: {
   181→    trigger: 'Threshold breaches';
   182→    channels: ['Email', 'Dashboard', 'Webhook'];
   183→    examples: ['Drift > 10%', 'Maintenance overdue'];
   184→  };
   185→}
   186→```
   187→
   188→## Key Design Principles
   189→
   190→### Separation of Concerns
   191→
   192→```typescript
   193→interface SeparationOfConcerns {
   194→  principle: 'Each component has single responsibility';
   195→
   196→  examples: {
   197→    solverOrchestrator: 'Only manages solver execution';
   198→    assetService: 'Only manages asset data';
   199→    apiLayer: 'Only handles HTTP concerns';
   200→  };
   201→
   202→  benefits: [
   203→    'Easier testing',
   204→    'Independent deployment',
   205→    'Clear ownership'
   206→  ];
   207→}
   208→```
   209→
   210→### Solver Abstraction
   211→
   212→```typescript
   213→interface SolverAbstraction {
   214→  principle: 'Business logic independent of solver choice';
   215→
   216→  implementation: {
   217→    interface: 'Common SolverAdapter interface';
   218→    adapters: ['HiGHSAdapter', 'CPSATAdapter', 'HeuristicAdapter'];
   219→    selection: 'Runtime based on problem characteristics';
   220→  };
   221→
   222→  benefits: [
   223→    'Switch solvers without code changes',
   224→    'A/B test solver performance',
   225→    'Fallback on solver failures'
   226→  ];
   227→}
   228→
   229→interface SolverAdapter {
   230→  solve(problem: SchedulingProblem): Promise<ScheduleSolution>;
   231→  interrupt(): void;
   232→  getStatus(): SolverStatus;
   233→}
   234→
   235→class HiGHSAdapter implements SolverAdapter {
   236→  async solve(problem: SchedulingProblem): Promise<ScheduleSolution> {
   237→    // Convert to HiGHS model and solve
   238→  }
   239→}
   240→
   241→class CPSATAdapter implements SolverAdapter {
   242→  async solve(problem: SchedulingProblem): Promise<ScheduleSolution> {
   243→    // Convert to CP-SAT model and solve
   244→  }
   245→}
   246→```
   247→
   248→### Event-Driven Updates
   249→
   250→```typescript
   251→interface EventDrivenDesign {
   252→  principle: 'React to changes asynchronously';
   253→
   254→  events: {
   255→    assetMileageUpdated: 'Triggers drift recalculation';
   256→    scheduleGenerated: 'Triggers notification and cache update';
   257→    maintenanceCompleted: 'Triggers next event scheduling';
   258→  };
   259→
   260→  implementation: {
   261→    broker: 'Redis pub/sub or message queue';
   262→    handlers: 'Idempotent event processors';
   263→    retry: 'Dead letter queue for failures';
   264→  };
   265→}
   266→```
   267→
   268→### Horizontal Scalability
   269→
   270→```typescript
   271→interface ScalabilityDesign {
   272→  principle: 'Scale out by adding instances';
   273→
   274→  stateless: {
   275→    apiServers: 'Any instance can handle any request';
   276→    session: 'Stored in Redis, not memory';
   277→  };
   278→
   279→  stateful: {
   280→    database: 'Single source of truth';
   281→    solverJobs: 'Queued and processed by workers';
   282→  };
   283→
   284→  scaling: {
   285→    readHeavy: 'Add read replicas';
   286→    writeHeavy: 'Partition by tenant/fleet';
   287→    computeHeavy: 'Scale solver workers';
   288→  };
   289→}
   290→```
   291→
   292→## Technology Stack Recommendations
   293→
   294→### Backend
   295→
   296→```typescript
   297→interface BackendStack {
   298→  runtime: {
   299→    primary: 'Node.js with TypeScript';
   300→    rationale: 'Type safety, async performance, ecosystem';
   301→    alternative: 'Python for ML-heavy features';
   302→  };
   303→
   304→  framework: {
   305→    api: 'Hono or Fastify';
   306→    rationale: 'Lightweight, fast, TypeScript-native';
   307→  };
   308→
   309→  database: {
   310→    primary: 'PostgreSQL 16+';
   311→    extensions: ['TimescaleDB for metrics', 'pg_cron for jobs'];
   312→  };
   313→
   314→  cache: {
   315→    primary: 'Redis';
   316→    uses: ['Session', 'Rate limiting', 'Job queue'];
   317→  };
   318→
   319→  solver: {
   320→    mip: 'HiGHS via Python subprocess';
   321→    cp: 'OR-Tools via Python subprocess';
   322→    interface: 'JSON over stdin/stdout';
   323→  };
   324→}
   325→```
   326→
   327→### Frontend
   328→
   329→```typescript
   330→interface FrontendStack {
   331→  framework: {
   332→    primary: 'React 18+';
   333→    meta: 'Next.js or Remix for SSR';
   334→  };
   335→
   336→  visualization: {
   337→    charts: 'ECharts or Recharts';
   338→    schedules: 'Custom Gantt component';
   339→    maps: 'Leaflet for fleet tracking';
   340→  };
   341→
   342→  state: {
   343→    server: 'TanStack Query';
   344→    client: 'Zustand for UI state';
   345→  };
   346→}
   347→```
   348→
   349→### Infrastructure
   350→
   351→```typescript
   352→interface InfrastructureStack {
   353→  containers: {
   354→    runtime: 'Docker';
   355→    orchestration: 'Kubernetes or Docker Compose';
   356→  };
   357→
   358→  cloud: {
   359→    compute: 'AWS ECS/GCP Cloud Run/Azure Container Apps';
   360→    database: 'Managed PostgreSQL';
   361→    storage: 'S3/GCS/Azure Blob';
   362→  };
   363→
   364→  observability: {
   365→    logging: 'Structured JSON logs';
   366→    metrics: 'Prometheus + Grafana';
   367→    tracing: 'OpenTelemetry';
   368→  };
   369→}
   370→```
   371→
   372→## Security Considerations
   373→
   374→### Authentication and Authorization
   375→
   376→```typescript
   377→interface SecurityDesign {
   378→  authentication: {
   379→    method: 'JWT with refresh tokens';
   380→    provider: 'Auth0, Clerk, or custom';
   381→    mfa: 'Recommended for production';
   382→  };
   383→
   384→  authorization: {
   385→    model: 'Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)';
   386→    roles: ['Admin', 'Planner', 'Operator', 'Viewer'];
   387→    granularity: 'Fleet-level or asset-level';
   388→  };
   389→
   390→  dataProtection: {
   391→    atRest: 'Database encryption';
   392→    inTransit: 'TLS 1.3';
   393→    pii: 'Minimize storage, encrypt sensitive fields';
   394→  };
   395→}
   396→```
   397→
   398→### API Security
   399→
   400→```typescript
   401→interface ApiSecurity {
   402→  rateLimit: '100 requests/minute per user';
   403→  validation: 'Zod schemas for all inputs';
   404→  cors: 'Whitelist allowed origins';
   405→  audit: 'Log all write operations';
   406→}
   407→```
   408→
   409→## Deployment Architecture
   410→
   411→### Production Topology
   412→
